Here's a quick shot I got in Venice one day with the RX100. I use that camera a lot for quick “street photos” — it's so darn fast and easy to use that I can get super-sharp and quick photos. I think it takes like 16 pictures in a second or something so you can be sure to have a lot to choose from. I guess it kind of feels like cheating to take so many photos… but I think the use of any kind of artifice in a creative process is noble! :) - Trey Ratcliff Click here to read the rest of this post at the Stuck in Customs blog.
